# PowerShell Shell Command Rules

The shell in this workspace is **PowerShell on Windows**. Bash syntax does NOT work here.

## Heredoc / Multiline Strings

PowerShell does NOT support bash heredoc (`<<'EOF' ... EOF`).

### Git commit with multiline message

❌ BAD — bash heredoc (breaks in PowerShell):
```bash
git commit -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
My message
EOF
)"
```

✅ GOOD — PowerShell here-string piped to `git commit -F -`:
```powershell
$msg = @"
Subject line here

- Bullet one
- Bullet two
"@
$msg | git commit -F -
```

## General multiline strings

Use PowerShell here-strings (`@" ... "@`) — the closing `"@` must be at column 0:

```powershell
$text = @"
line one
line two
"@
```

## Unix/Linux commands that do NOT exist in PowerShell

NEVER use these in the Shell tool — use the alternatives shown:

| ❌ Linux command | ✅ PowerShell / Cursor tool alternative |
|---|---|
| `head -N file` | Use the **Read tool** with `limit: N` |
| `tail -N file` | Use the **Read tool** with `offset: -N` |
| `cat file` | Use the **Read tool** |
| `grep pattern file` | Use the **Grep tool** |
| `find . -name "*.js"` | Use the **Glob tool** |
| `touch file` | `New-Item -ItemType File file` |
| `rm file` | `Remove-Item file` |
| `cp src dst` | `Copy-Item src dst` |
| `mv src dst` | `Move-Item src dst` |
| `mkdir -p dir` | `New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force dir` |
| `echo "text" > file` | Use the **Write tool** |
| `sed`, `awk` | Use the **StrReplace tool** or **Read + Write** |
| `export VAR=val` | `$env:VAR = "val"` |

**Rule**: If a task only needs to read or search a file, always prefer the dedicated Cursor tools (Read, Grep, Glob) over any shell command. Reserve the Shell tool for commands that genuinely require the terminal (git, npm, node, etc.).

## Other common pitfalls

- Use `;` not `&&` to chain commands (or use separate Shell calls)
- Quoting: use double quotes `"..."` for strings with variables; single quotes `'...'` for literals
